The paper deals with using external linguistic knowledge to improve the performance of recurrent neural networks in text comprehension tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for encoding graphs as explicit memory in recurrent neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies the proposed model to several text comprehension tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper achieves state-of-the-art results on benchmarks such as CNN and LAMBADA, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
